  "response": "No, you generally cannot directly use a Jio 4G SIM in a 3G-only handset for data connectivity. Here's why:\n\n*   **Technology Differences:** Jio's network is primarily based on 4G LTE technology. 3G handsets are designed to connect to older 3G networks (like UMTS, HSPA). The hardware in a 3G phone simply isn't built to understand or connect to a 4G LTE network.\n*   **Voice Calling:** Even if you somehow got the SIM to register on the network, voice calling may be an issue. Jio uses VoLTE (Voice over LTE) for voice calls. 3G phones don't support VoLTE. So, standard voice calls likely won't work.\n\n**In summary:** While the SIM might register on the network in some limited cases (usually just enough to see a signal bar), you won't get usable data speeds or reliable voice service with a Jio 4G SIM in a 3G-only phone. You'll need a 4G-compatible phone to properly use a Jio SIM.",
